caption: We were basically walking thinking of trying a new place for burgers! Found the place in Google maps being like 1 block away from it. The Double Cheese burger and the outrageous burger were excellent. Friendly staff, good service and tasty burgers!
Great place! Awesome food! Very good people.

I come to this outstanding restaurant once a month because I love the good air that is outline this restaurant. The team is exceptionally cordial and professional. The service is extremely efficient. Most important, the food you eat is highly distinguished. I ate there many times and I was always happy. The cost is modest. I recommend this restaurant to my friends and family.
Ok nothing special
You must try this corn!!Seriously!! Just delicious  lovely place, the staff is nice! Enough of place between tables Great local spot!
Great service, peaceful setting.....love it..

Despite the strange Covid times, we were really excited to go sit outside at this cute spot for drinks — our server was extremely friendly and my dog joined us. We didn’t get to eat there but we had adult Capri suns — THEY DO THE TRICK! And it was very nice to feel somewhat normal again. Thanks Bar Basic!
Great food..relaxing atmosphere
Good vibe good food
Great food, nice people!
The food was delicious. I got the Texas brisket sandwich... It's indescribably tasty. Service was stellar, attentive, friendly
Good coffee and a really good BLT.
Great find. Casual, friendly, fast, good food and drinks

We were walking by and stumbled on this place - happy we did! We had great service and good drinks. Lots of veg options. Really loved the flavor and look of the veg empanada appetizer! Our impossible burgers were superb and the tater tots perfect! Missed the espresso coffee, as the shut down their machine at 9:00pm. Will certainly return...
The food was good (especially the fried sweet plantains) and a lot of veg options. A bit pricey and the drinks were all juice but would still return to try other food
Food was good, but I'm just not used to $17 burgers.
The place is just like my ex girlfriend.  Just basic

Lovely place with a stunning furniture. So good and such a great vibe! I had brunch there with a friend visiting from Jersey and we thoroughly enjoyed buttermilk fried chicken waffles with bloodymary. Everything was excellent we enjoyed every single bite of it. Glad we got in at 10am otherwise it would have been tricky to get a table. Around 11am this place got packed! The waiters were attentive though and friendly, so that's definitely a plus!
Spicy Paloma = really nice mezcal drink, just make sure to ask for the spicy rim  Gluten-free menu designations  Designated GF fryer  Good music  Friendly staff
Fun place and super friendly staff.

The food is great, and the beer selection is decent, but what stops this becoming a neighbourhood hangout is the staff. Customer service is poor, and service is slow. Staff spend more time talking to each other than serving customers. A real shame as the kitchen and the back-of-house staff are great.
Cool little spot for a beer and something quick to eat.
Great food options and unique drinks

Overall, it has a very cute vibe and homey feel to it, which I enjoyed. Loved their intensive cocktails menu with a focus on different types of margarita and mezcal.  Food wise, guacamole was super yum, pescado taco was really good, It was just so gooooood! Seriously enjoyed each and every bite of the dish and the density of the sauce & harmony in a plate was just perfect! Really need to go back to try it again.

Went here for dinner with one of my bros to catch up. This was my first time here, I found it through Yelp. I definitely recommend you check it out if you love Burger. Also if you enjoy good music.  The brisket was also top notch, up there with some of the best I've had. The pulled pork was the best I've ever had. I'm not usually one for pulled pork because what I've had hasn't been great but theirs is official.
Wonderful people

Yummy brunch at 2pm on a Saturday in early August. Great staff. Just very warm as they is no a/c , but we were fortunate enough to be seated by the front where the front was open to the outside. There were some fans on.
Great drinks, vibe, and excellent Mac and Cheese
Can’t wait to go back, al pastor is the bomb

Went with a few friends to have a quick brunch. We were excited about this new spot that we saw as we were walking down the street. Loved the scenery and vibes. We ordered our food and realized some of out items wasn't of our flavor. Talked to management because our waitress went on lunch and he was our server now. We politely explained that we were not too pleased with some of the food. He explained that once the food is made that we still have to pay for it (which is fine). He did not offer any type of accommodation seeing that we were not indulging in our food. We understood the policy but his delivery and lack of empathy was not customer service quality. Once our waitress returned from her break we explained to her the problem and how the manager at the time should have asked if there was anything he can do to make it better. She also could not accommodate us and the way she was talking to us seem as though she was trying to provoke us, which is not of our nature. She did offer to give us carry outs, which we accepted. In my opinion in a place of establishment like this there should have been better customer service and at least some type of accommodations if the customer still has to pay for their food. Thank you!
Great menu and service
The food continues to improve and the veggie burgers are awesome! It's a little expensive for 'basic' items but they're done right and it's convenient.
Great atmosphere, good food, drinks will come again
Amazing margs, kitchy af, incredible bartenders. Happy hour goes to 7...must have in my life and yours.
The cocktails are great. Food is 👌.
I don't know how the food is. After 15 minutes waiting to be attended, we left. It wasn't a busy day either.
Sweet potato fries were great, staff were nice too

Came here for lunch. They have a happy hour at the bar most of the day. The carnitas tacos were delicious, as was the queso dip. The place doesn't have AC though so it gets a little hot. That can be fixed with a beer!!
Great beer selection, good food! I recommend the happy hour beer and tacos!
Friendly staff, decent happy hour and good tacos.
Nice ambiance!  Fried fish was tasty.  Friends  did not love the special margaritas, and bench seating was a bit cramped for some.
The Eggs Benedict was the best my wife has ever had. I got the avocado toast scramble and it was outstanding. Their coffee was great -- all drip coffee is a well-made Americano..great brunch spot!
It was great. The bartender was really nice and attentive. But the music was too loud, the lights were too dim, and the neon lights provided a glaring contrast. Grumble grumble!
Good food, nice atmosphere.

Great idea, good reviews, but in reality... I have ordered a delivery to the office for many ppl, food (Farmer Salad) came in a box, not mixed and it is not possible to mix that salad in that box! The box is full of greens and a few pieces of tomatoes, cucumbers, etc. Another salad (Earthy Kale Salad) came in in the plastic box full of kale and a few cherry tomatoes halves (also not possible to mix).  QUESADILLA  is tiny!! The delivery guy is rude, asked for tips (tips were added to the bill online). 2 of the salads were missing, we called and the person on the phone referred us to Grubhub to request another driver (!). I would think they should fix the mistake they made, not us. According to other employees of the office Burger was good! So, salads are 1 star, Burgers are 5 star. But the whole experience is a decaffeinate "NO", will not order again. there are soooo many places around who are excellent in preparing food and caring for their clients. Please look at the pictures i posted, compare them with the ones on the website and keep in mind that the boxes with salads are FULL of greens and dusted with other ingredients on top. Absolutely tasteless.
Cute. Genourous fish and chips! Colorful interior. 80ies music
The ambiance the food everything was perfect. I loved the avocado toast. Tasted delicious and esthetically pleasing. Will be going back.

This is a hip place with a good selection of food and cocktails. I love the Ghibli theme on the drinks and with some of the artwork. I was pleasantly surprised with the size of my salad. Service was attentive and friendly. My boyfriend got a cookie to go and wouldn't stop talking about how gooey and perfect it was.
Great place. We take the kids often. Usually get the burger (delicious).
My favorite place for brunch!!! The chicken and waffles is to die for !
The best buttermilk chicken burger i have ever tasted! If you havent then you should! 😉👌💃💃
Average priced pints for the area. Good friendly service.
Good food 👌 the best sweet plantains around
Went during happy hour special. The server is attentive, the vibes is great, i love their margaritas cocktail with spicy rim which they squeezed the lime freshly on the spot. Delicious!
Very boring kale salad. The bellini was good though
Very cozy, awesome menu, artsy! Good for social or even reading/working. Definitely recommend

This cute and nicely decorated place has affordable and delicious Mexican brunch.  I was shocked at how excellent the chips and guacamole was $12.  Chips were fresh, crunchy and piping hot when it was served.  I had huevos egg benedict, it comes poached and smothered in a wonderful sauce with a side of salad.  It was delicious!!!!! My friends ordered Queso Breakfast Burrito, which he thinks is amazing, mouthful of flavors and a pool of cheese from the queso sauce.  Coffee is freshly grind coffee by Stumptown $3, not pricey but really good. Hisbiscus tea is refreshing as expected. Also, for $7 more you can get a glass of mimosa. We had the place almost all up to ourselves on a Monday morning.  The place is clean and cool with a really good vibe.  I will be back for sure. This park slope restaurant  knocks it outta the park.

Hey!! If you haven't tried this spot, you need to get there fast. Honestly, you should go ahead band call me "chicken& waffle". I've been to so many chicken and waffle places over the past year, oh my. Well, Bar Basic didn't disappoint. The waffle was not your typical one you get with a chicken and waffle meal. First of all it was and in the traditional Belgian waffle style. I thoroughly enjoyed the waffle and the chicken was moist and right out the hot oil. My friend had the fish Po' Boy and she enjoyed her meal as well.  Bar Basic is not some fancy spot, it's very mom-n-pop and so you may have to wait a bit to be seated but because it is a mom and pop type restaurant your getting all that tender love and care in every dish. Bar Basic was recommended to me a few months ago and I finally got a chance to experience it and like I said in the very beginning, it didn't disappoint. I shall return and you should get off your hind parts and get those thighs over there right now. Enjoy

Located in north Park Slope on 7th Avenue, few blocks away from Barclay Center. Surprisingly, there is no wait for Brunch on a Saturday morning (as you might expect).  Once you're seated and you peruse the menu, you might realize you made the right decision in coming here. The interior is cute and simple, with reclaimed wood table, the spacing between chairs is not tight and you have a lot of room to move around or stretching your arms.  I went with a popular choice, the Buttermilk Fried Chicken Burger (Pressed classic potato bun sandwich with chicken, coleslaw, pickled, & chipotle mayo), and we all shared a few sides like cilantro lime rice, general tso's wing, guacamole and chips, and fries. First off, the Buttermilk Fried Chicken Burger was heaven. The chicken, creamy chipotle mayo, and pickled cabbage's textures blended beautifully without any of the flavors overpowering each other. I have never tried General Tso' Wing before but if you're a fan of wing you must give this one a shot at least. I washed it all down with a glass of their fresh agua pine juice, which was solid and recommended.  Our waitress was quick and accurate. All of the staff moved with a motivated frenetic energy. There are many brunch option places in Brooklyn, but Bar Basic should be near the top of your list.  Also did i mentioned this restaurant is a kid's friendly restaurant and they have stroller parking area.
Nice small place on 7th Ave.
Dripping with ambiance. Happy to have such a vibey local spot that has good eats, drinks & board games to keep all ages busy.
Great vibe, better food and the owners are nice people.
Nice and intimate  setting. Courteous and speedy service. Come here for a great brunch!
Always a pleasant place to dine. The food the music. Can never go wrong with Bar basic
Stopped by for drinks on NYE, nice atmosphere and good cocktails!
Good place

After a lovely weekend in New York, this was the perfect place to stop for dinner before hitting the road. The service was great, food is delicious, and the ambiance could not be better! We'll be back!
All was great: the food, the service, the ambiance, and willingness of the staff to accomodate dinner with two small babies—greatly appreciate it!

This is a great trendy spot for special occasions. They also can accommodate larger groups since the space is large in itself.  Bar Basic is known for its burger and taco dishes, and their buttermilk fried chicken burger is one of my favorite. I also recently tried their chicken satay dish which had some interesting flavor.  The restrooms, located down the hallway, are sleek on the outside and look endless cool while inside.

What not to love this place! Great service, nice decor, and good vibe. Went there with a group of friends, we ordered their seasonal tap beer and cocktails. they have a great happy hour special, all beers $5 and cocktails $7. BTW, the might wings is out of this world, it is a must try.  I will be back soon to try the rest of their food menu.  Great place to hanging out with friends! I recommend trying all their tap beer, avoid nothing!
Good service, nice place to hang out, and the coffee was good.  Had the kale salad and it left something to be desired. Fried chicken was awesome though!
Great atmosphere, amazing team and great Americana food.
Nicely decorated: cozy & cute. Friendly staff Delicious brunch options

Was visiting new york 2 weeks ago with few of my friends. Got the hangover cure with basic margaritas. Let me tell you those margaritas were on point. They were very generous with the tequila and fresh ingredients were definitely used. I can tell I'm from mexico. I know a thing or two about tequila and a fair share of hang overs ja ja. This place had the cutest decor, will be back if I can.

This place is awesome! Love their brunch menu which you can get a glass of mimosa with any entree order for $7, this is a steal! I ordered adult grilled cheese with tomato soup, it was amazing. The plate looks gorgeous, they plated the grilled cheese on top of a wooden plate and a bowl of tomato soup. My boyfriend ordered hangover cure and one of their fall cocktail, apple hot toddy. He absolutely love it.  All food and cocktails are amazing, the service is excellent, friendly, and welcoming. My waiter comes back every once a while to check on us. You won’t be disappointed.  By the way, i love their decor and the vibe just un-believeably chill. I went there on Saturday which they have live music which is a extra touch to our experience. Good vibes.  This place is a solid 5 star from me and the fall apple cider mimosa was fantastic, it's fresh and earthy!!!! I can't wait to come back.
Fresh delicous salads and ice teas! Very very good !
Love the environment  and decor here.  Very chill vibe.
Lots of craft tap beers selection, especially the dogfish head liquid truth serum Ipa hoppy and balance, great service and friendly bartender
Great food and lovely, humorous staff. Waiter even sprinted after a customer had left to give back credit card because they left it in the payment machine!!
It’s good, but it seems every time I go prices go up which is a little annoying since it’s such a fun chill spot.

i am all about supporting small and local businesses. This place have to be one of the best restuarant on 7th Avenue. Farm to table ingredient, seasonal menu, perfect cocktails, stumptown coffee, craft beers on tap and chill vibes.  You can't find any place that's better than this spot. This place delivered hip vibes, urban, cozy atmosphere, cool music, and movie night. This gastropub stands out from the remaining restaurants on 7th Avenue, you can look no further. This place is paradise in heaven. i finally find myself a place to hangout with my friends that fit into my character. life is good.

substantial, deliciousdishes that will fill up your heart and stomach. My boyfriend recommend this placeand i could.not agree me. our server isvery attenetive, friendly and welcoming.  we orderd buttermilk chicken waffle, it came out pipingout and buttery.i really enjoyed the meal.
Nice spot. Excellent breakfast burrito, fries.

The place is just so good. Rustic, cozy and reclaimed wood bar. Three friends and I had a fantastic visit to the Bar Basic. The drinks are awesome, and the food might be even better. For food, we ordered:  Buttermilk fried chicken burger Roasted jerk chicken Satay chicken The bird Mighty wings Pesto cauliflower Kitchen sink fries  The satay chicken were one of the best thing I've eaten, ever, and the buttermilk fried chicken burger was my second favorite. Nothing should be skip from their food menu, all food is amazing. Finally and most importantly, you can actually have a conversation here.  Definitely a new favorite spot.  The service was super friendly and the bathroom had major vibes.  Yes, once you go to the bathroom you'll understand why it deserved a mention.
The food was delicious, small and cozy

The basil strawberry lemonade was the best part.  Kale salad came with a ton of lettuce but very little toppings and a tiny cup of dressing on the side. I do not want to mix my own salad, especially kale.  bathrooms were disgusting - they look like .they have not been cleaned in days
Awesome food!!!!!!

I had an Organic Quinoa Salad from here yesterday. It was ok, it just didn’t have any meat so within an hour I was starving. The quinoa and orange slices were different from my usual salad and I liked the citrus based dressing. The tortillas were a nice bonus. But I just wasn’t fulfilled in the end. The Grubhub lunch menu is rather boring and offers little variety and choices. The fourth star is for the eco-friendly container.

Never felt compelled to write a critical review but here we go... I ordered a draft beer and it tasted like they hadn't cleaned the lines of the tap in a while. My girlfriend ordered the chicken tacos, which were pretty bad. The tortillas were from the freezer with a very unpleasant chemical aftertaste and the plantain chips with which they were served were absolutely inedible - very dry and bland. I had the brisket sandwich, which was honestly pretty good but way too fatty/greasy which didn't sit well at all.  I wish they would pare down the menu and do fewer items really well.
Yes just yes
Great Food.  Every new dish I try is great.  Tried most things on the menu at this point.

This place is usually packed on the weekends but we came here in a Monday afternoon. Be warned, this is not diet food, however they do offer a lot of healthy option dishes. But rest assured, you'll leave satisfied and happy. I meant really happy with boozy.  We ordered the half bird, shrimp gumbo, and fish taco. Everything was amazing, especially the fish taco. It was extremely crisp on the outside and juicy on the inside. The shrimp gumbo is full of flavors. You can't miss this spot.  It's not my first time here but it never disappoints. The whisky sour is amazing on everything as well.
Very friendly service. No drinks allowed on the patio yet, but when the weather is nice the front doors are open. The food was served to us so quickly you would think the chef was psychic.
Good food, good service. I'll be back.
The food was really good and the service was amazing. Would definitely make this my chill spot.
(Translated by Google) Warm welcome, good IPA beers, and beautiful decor  (Original) Accueil chaleureux, bonnes bières IPA, et belle déco

Uninspired food, BLT was primarily mayo, fried green tomatoes made without pablo and served with syrup...disappointed after walking by and seeing the menu and reviews I was genuinely excited to try this spot.
Great menu

Great spot for a good beer and southern food. My partner got the Texas Brisket sandwich and I got the friend chicken sandwich. Both were delicious! They also have healthier options which sound delicious like a tuna stuffed avocado. Will come back again!
Extremely nice staff but overwhelmed. Food took almost an hour and my friends meal came out ten minutes before mine so he had finished by the time mine arrived.
very mediocre food.
Very nice selection of food. Very well prepared. Brunch is very nice. Chicken and waffles is great.
Yummy food. Great staff.

I've been meaning to review this place ever since they opened.  After having about 28 five star experiences I've decided that I need to share this restaurant/bar as well.  The owner of this restaurant kept all of the positive aspects built up and added a Southern chill type of vibe with a laid back theme. The tables and chair made by reclaimed wood, the bar counter also made by reclaimed support beam wood. I love their concept of sustainability and recycled, reused the materials. The restaurant is surrounded by live plants and flowers, it is liked a indoor garden. Absolutely stunning and inviting.  I recognize the quality ingredients used and that, at the sacrifice of cost percentages, they serve ample and well balanced entrees that over-satisfy an apatite as large as mine (a 130+ lb triathlete who needs her k-calories;)  To sum this up, go there and see for yourself, you will not be dissatisfied with this new addition to Park Slope! I am all about support small local business and i think you should too.  Favorite items: Buttermilk Fried Chicken Waffle (sweet and savory) Basic Burger (love the pickled cabbage) Mighty Wing (a MUST, if you love wing, you will fall in love with this) Old Fashioned Cocktails (so smooth, a MUST have) Coffee (they use La Colombe Roaster coffee, really good espresso drink) Shrimp Gumbo (their signature dish, rich and thick)  Memorable Staff: Nick (Server) Ryan (Bar Tender)

Banana waffle is indeed delicious....I cannot get the taste of the dulce de leche off my mind. Because that is exactly how delicious the banana waffle tasted while having Brunch at Bar Basic! It was the epitome of food greatness but I will come back to that in a bit....  Bar Basic is located in the north Park Slope of Brooklyn which is quite a quiet and family friendly place. They are newly opened in the area, an great addition to the neighbor. We decided to come here for brunch after I went on Yelp and saw all of the fantastic looking food in people's postings. Once we arrived at Bar Basic, we were definitely able to confirm not only great looking but fabulously smelling food at the time when you entered! I will never be able to verbalize just how wonderful the aromas were that emanated from the various dishes. All we did was ooh and aah at every single plate that went by us....It is a true testament to them having a extraordinary selection of options on their brunch menu!  The friendly hostess informed us that we will have to wait about 20 minutes, however we were probably seated in about 10 minutes which was nice. Bar Basic staff provided prompt service as we received water, coffee and mimosa quickly. Thanks to Peter and Nick for being so lovely!  Ok....so I had the Banana waffle w / side of organic spring salad. Banana waffle is the best tasting buttery pieces of waffle that I have ever had! Crispy around the edges and soft, fluffy goodness in the middle. Oh my.....the homemade dulce de leche syrup and marvelous walnut that complimented the waffle made it perfection throughout each and every bite! I was also told about and got to taste some of egg benedict, perfect porched egg and creamy hollandaise sauce....Spectacular! The dried roasted shiitake mushroom and spinach went well with the egg benedict with just perfect amount of braised pulled pork end. The dish just lovely.  We had such a pleasurable experience...I need some more of that banana waffle in my life! For the advice, you have to wait roughly 20 minutes for the waffle since it is made to order. It is totally worth the wait. I promised.

We've come here a few times since they first opened. The owners/staff we interacted with seemed genuinely nice. The burgers and food were just alright. We went back a few times hoping the burgers would be better since the Park Slope area by far needs better ones, but it hasn't improved. Burgers have potential, but they all had this sweetness to it that was a little odd. Might be in the burger, or the sauce but it tastes like a bunch of sugar was added. The veggies burger, Basic, Chicken, Pork sliders all suffered from this. The buttermilk chicken burger was a let down as well. The chicken quality/flavor was lacking and came across as nothing special. They serve breakfast now so we may try it. I just hope trying this place again isn't a waste again. Decent place, but not anything memorable.
Just ordered from Bar Basic on Amazon restaurant. I ordered the buttermilk chicken sandwich and mac and cheese poppers. And I was in LOVE. OMG, it was delicious.

The wings here used to be amazing. This was when they first opened, but now they're kinda different, the chicken is grey, slimy texture, and undercooked. If they fix this problem  I'd eat there wayyyy more often. Other than that, the food is a little greasy but that's ok, overall good food but could be better.

Great food, good drinks, and awesome atmosphere. They also have wifi and an awwwwwweeeeesome host - has super really nice and responsive. Try the cereal milk and the Totoro drinks! They also make a great old fashioned if you want a more traditional drink.  The only knock I have is the food could be a little "hotter".... BUT that doesn't detract from the taste or the excellent dining/drinking experience.

We went hungry -- we left buzzed and stuffed with food to take home. A night to put in the books for sure.  We ordered lots of food here, but I stilled wish we could have tried everything off their menu!! Everything was so flavorful, no items were the same as the other. There were two large groups dining while we were there. The staff was fun, and very nice. The music was sooooo good!  If I could go back in time and recreate how awesome this experience was.. I would in a heartbeat! i love this place.
Just stopped in for a quick drink but seemed fun! Not cash only as some sources suggest. They have trivia once a month on Monday’s. Also the food looked good

The entire experience here was a disappointment. When I went, the restaurant was understaffed (1 waiter and no busboys), and he was completely overwhelmed. My party and I ordered 2 burgers medium rare and 1 medium well, and they all came medium well. The two kids I was with ordered waffles, which never came. The first batch were made with the cheese when the kids ordered cheese on the side, and the second time, he said there was something wrong with the batter so they were unservable. The waiter neglected to tell us any of this until it was too late to order something else and the rest of us had finished our burgers. Lastly, we had to ask for everything that a waiter should already be on top of, like silverware, water, napkins etc. 1 star SOLELY for the fries. I will not be surprised if the restaurant goes out of business.

Arrived for breakfast/brunch and was pleasantly surprised at how quickly we were seated and attended to.  Our waiter greeted us with the warmest smile. After taking our drink requests, he reviewed Bar Basic most popular brunch items to include brief descriptions of them. We were given just enough time to look over the entire menu before he returned to take our orders. Everything on the menu read very appetizing. Ultimately I chose the Shrimp Gumbo.  The best way to describe it are in the words of  Rachael Ray who said, " it's like a party in my mouth." The dish was flavorful, not lacking anything that I could think of. The gumbo were thick and smooth as I like, the shrimp prepared perfectly!  I have absolutely no complaints. My next visit will be next month to celebrate my father's birthday. Let's hope that he enjoys it as much as I did today.

Family owned, independent and local owner. Sophisticated twists on typical Southern cuisine join, many bourbon-based, in the pretty rustic-chic dining room of this happening in North Park Slope. This restaurant tucked away just enough from busy streets and attended by friendly servers. Few blocks away from grand army plaza and barclay center. Great addition to the neighbor.  I ordered the buttermilk fried chicken with red velvet waffle, the chicken was juicy and full of spice.  This is the place if you want your soul to be satisfied.

Great burger and good portion.  This place has better burger and fries compared to other Burger stores.  The restaurant has a great atmosphere!  I'd recommend to any of my friends.  By the way, don't forget to try their shrimp gumbo. It is dope and full of flavors. Helpful?

The Milkshake was great! The burger and fries were good, when ordered they asked for Burger tempts they all came out well done when ordered medium and medium rare, but they were still tasty! Would definitely recommend!
(Translated by Google) Very nice site rich food  (Original) Sitio muy bonito rica comida
Chicken sandwich was pretty good, and the tots were excellent. The vibe of the place is pretty cool, love the wooden plates. Simple menu.

Went here on a double date, and my goodness people! The food and service was spectacular! We ordered the buttermilk fried chicken burger. It is to die for! My crew and I talked so much that the staff kept coming to check on us and making us laugh.  This is THE perfect spot for a beautiful sunny day in BK! And the staff is so welcoming.
